The paper deals with problems related to directed graphs and mobile agents, which are common topics in the subfield of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of Steiner trees and the study of tractability and complexity suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), game theory (cs.GT), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the problem of clearing subgraphs by mobile agents involves optimization and algorithmic techniques, which are also relevant to the subfield of robotics (cs.RO).
